text: An election happened on November 3, 2020 to elect a Senator from the U.S. state of Delaware. The main two people in the election were Chris Coons (Democratic Party) and Lauren Witzke (Republican Party). Mark Turley (Independent Party) and Nadine Frost (Libertarian Party) were also in the election. Coons won the election and stayed as Senator. Primary elections happened on September 15, 2020. The Democratic Party primary was between Chris Coons and Jessica Scarane, which Coons won. The Republican Party primary was between Lauren Witzke and James DeMartino, which Witzke won. ==Democratic Party primary== ==Republican Party primary== ==Other candidates== ===Libertarian Party=== ====Nominee==== *Nadine Frost, Libertarian candidate for U.S. Senate in 2018 ===Independent Party of Delaware=== ====Nominee==== *Mark Turley, small business owner ==Results== ==References== Category:2020 United States Senate elections Category:2020s in Delaware
title: 2020 United States Senate election in Delaware
